      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Plenty of win chances. BAYSIDE (4) has been given a few weeks between runs after disappointing last time on the Synthetic at Devonport. Much better draw, drops in weight and has won here. Will be winding up late. TRIBAL COUNCIL (3) ran a better race and finished 1.3 lengths away in fourth last time out over 1400m here after racing on speed. Well placed with the big claim and among the main chances with a repeat. LADY FERN (8) is knocking on the door after just missing a lip here last time over 1200m. Another big run is expected. GEEGEES DOWNPOUR (5) doesn't win out of turn but ran a nice race last time out over 1200m at this track, finishing fourth and beaten 2 lengths. Best figures measure up. Set to run well again off the inside. CRYSTAL MOONBEAM (6) looks a win chance as well. Best form is this course and distance and should be in the finish.",
